    "analysis": "Previous scan computed global P95 thresholds for all (component, KPI) groups and found widespread short spikes in request/row_count (traces and logs) starting ~21:25–21:36 UTC and correlated memory increases across many services later in the window. error_logs.csv is empty and log.error_count stayed at zero, so there is no direct error-log signal. Candidate services to investigate (per task) include checkoutservice, currencyservice, emailservice, productcatalogservice, recommendationservice. We still need to perform fault identification (consecutive anomalous sub-series) on metric KPIs for these candidate services to determine which service-level fault(s) could be the root cause and when they began. Traces and logs will be used afterwards to disambiguate if multiple service-level faults are found.",
